    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-06-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-06-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="1427"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1427">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/348.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Special Agent <persName type="from">Carothers</persName> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San Antonio</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-06-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 28, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: When I was in Saltillo on my last visit to Mr.
                    Carranza, his sub-Secretary of Foreign Relations, Mr. Fabela, was very anxious
                    to have me write you regarding the diplomatic representations made <pb
                        facs="0939" n="823" xml:id="pg_823"/> in behalf of other nations, to see if
                    it would not be possible to have the diplomatic representatives in Washington
                    make them direct to Carranza, through the Foreign Relations office, as England
                    has been doing for several months. England has appointed Mr. Miles as Vice
                    Consul in El Paso, and is obtaining very satisfactory results through his
                    representations. If you could induce the Spanish Ambassador to do the same, I am
                    sure that Carranza would not only appreciate it, but would concede very promptly
                    to requests made by the Ambassador.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">G. C. Carothers</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
